OmniArea

public OmniArea(java.lang.String userInput,
                double longitude,
                double latitude,
                double proximityDistance)
         throws DataTypeValidationException
Parameters:
userInput - address entered by user. Stored separately.
longitude - number degrees east of Greenwich. Values are between -180 and 180. Represents latitude of userInput.
latitude - number of degrees above equator. Values are between -90 and 90. Represents longitude of userInput.
proximityDistance - the radius of the circular area around the indicated longitude and latitude. Value must be >= 0.
Throws:
DataTypeValidationException - if values of longitude, latitude, or proximityDistance are improper.
